      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "0cae8a279cc3f5c4",
      "text": "Ego can choose to look at the thinking of the other (alter ego) as if this were possible. We assume the other thinks. Communication systems  must understand communicating itself as an action, and only in this sense does the action become a necessary part of the system's self-reproduction from moment to moment. It is therefore never wrong, but one-sided [\"one way\"], for a communication system to conceive of itself as a system of action. It is only through [[Action]] that communication becomes fixed as a simple [[Event]] at a point in [[Time]]."
